{
  "stem": "18102.5",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "I remember there-- since we were on the outskirts of the city, I remember seeing the tanks enter, and then the army following the tanks, and so forth.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "But eventually, we moved back to our bungalow, because there was no longer any bombings, and there was no longer any point in living away from the house.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "No sooner did we come back to our own home in Bialystok that the Germans-- gestapo did come to search for my father.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "He was, of course, gone.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And they searched through the clothes.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "They asked lots of questions of my mother, and-- and so forth.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And it was quite a frightening affair.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "But eventually, they left because my father just wasn't there.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] In fact, we didn't know where my father had left.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And we not-- we did not hear from him for the several weeks that the Germans occupied Bialystok.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And at some point in the history of these events, Stalin made a pact with Hitler to create a truce between the two countries and divide Poland, part to the Russians and part to the Germans.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "Bialystock was supposed to be handed over to the Russians.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And so on a given Saturday afternoon when this was to happen, the German army marched out, and the Russian army marched in.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And I recall my mother taking me to the main street where these events which she told me would be quite historic were about to occur.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And of course, everyone was lined in the streets.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "The entire Bialystok came out to watch.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "And sure enough, the German army marched out.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "And within an hour after that, the first of the Russian army started to march in.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "And of course, the population of Bialystok was grateful.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
